verbose_text: Augmented inflammation and apoptosis were associated with stronger activation of TLR4 mediated signal transduction; the phosphorylation of IkappaBalpha, JNK, ERK1/2, and p38, and nuclear translocation of NF-kappaB p65 induced by LPS were further increased by overexpression of ROCK1.
